HAS-A-RELATIONSHIP

1.Basically, it means that an instance of the one class has a reference to the instance of another class or the other instance of the same class. 
2.This relationship helps to minimize the duplication of code as well as the bugs.

A. Aggregation
    1. which It means when a class contains reference of another class known to have aggregation.
    2. In other words, class A has-a relationship with class B, if class A has a reference to an instance of class B.

B. Composition

    1. Has a relationship in Java is known to be as Composition. It is used for code reusability. 
    2. Composition is a restricted form of Aggregation in which two entities are highly dependent on each other.
    3.  It represents part-of relationship.
    4. In composition, both the entities are dependent on each other.
    5. When there is a composition between two entities, the composed object cannot exist without the other entity.

